What a great bar and restaurant!  A distinctly oak wood bar adorned with chandeliers for a perfect urban politically savvy DC establishment. The big screen TVs can be easily viewed from anywhere in bar or dining area for a perfect game day to a nice dinner experience with family, friends and colleagues. The bar is huge, offering a special whiskey array with local as well nationally popular labels. The food selection is excellent American fair with a twist cooked by a talented kitchen team...The service is excellent lead by Manager Antonio who is impressively attentive and polite as well as being highly knowledgeable about his menu, bar and staff. I would highly recommend this restaurant for any occasion from game day with the boys to a business event or dinner with family and friends.

I have been to the Hawk n Dove I don't know how many times and always had great service and drinks. However their parent company's recent refusal to abide by DC health and safety mandates during a public health emergency has fundamentally changed how I view this business. Hopefully they will do something to earn my, and others business back. In the mean time, I will miss the wonderful staff and memories at the Hawk and Dove.  Update: after swift government and public backlash, the parent company decided to comply. However for me the damage has been done for now.

Very nice hidden treat near the Library of Congress and I highly recommend coming here. Price is also very reasonable.

We came in with a huge party, which may not have been explained in the planning stages, so they just gave us "open seating" and told our party of 100+ people to find a place. Took the servers a while to make sure everyone was taken care of but the food came quickly and was very flavourful. Bar was out of every other liquor we ordered. Then they tried to bill every one at each table on one ticket instead of providing separate bills. Was a little crowded and a little loud, but given the situation a pleasant experience.

The "reborn" Hawk 'n' Dove is not what it used to be but is still quite a great place. Just right adjacent to Capitol Hill it offers a large variety of drinks and quality bar food dishes in a comfortable, clean, relaxed but still upscale fashion. They have an elevated bar area, a main dining area, and a second floor too. The steaks and beers are great and the prices not bad at all. It's a comfortable place overall that strikes a balance between a 'sophisticated' DC bar and a dive bar - it has a casual feel to it but is definitely has enough of a refined sense too to it to not feel grimmy/rowdy.

The bartender (Gerardo) first put the rocks glass in the ice to scoop up ice (super dangerous since glass can break - this is bartending 101) then he poured the bourbon on top of the ice, then sprinkled bitters on top.  WTF?  Where is the muddling?  No cherry, orange slice, sugar cube with bitters muddled at all.  Weird.  I got Basil Hayden's and it was $17.60 and he didn't provide an itemized receipt.  The whole experience left me feeling ripped off, I closed out and left.

A poor excuse for the original!  The original Hawk ‘n’  Dove was a treasured neighborhood dive bar.  The new iteration tries too hard to be “hip.”  The food is decidedly average, the decor is bland, and the prices are insanely high.

Decent but could be better. The good: crab dip is excellent. They served deviled eggs which were also good. The wings were poor. Not crispy at all. Good flavor but soft and squishy. Ordered a Medium burger and it came out as hockey puck well done. Fried chicken sandwich was chicken fingers on a bun and they were over cooked to death and bland. I wanted a chicken breast sandwich not chicken dried out fingers. They forgot the bacon on all three sandwiches. Forgot the mayo. Service was attentive until we got our food and then we never saw our server again. Had to flag down someone else to go get her to bring the bacon and mayo and then she took forever to bring it. The decor was nice, the prices are reasonable but the over cooked entrees squishy wings, and inattentive service warrants three stars. But I’d be willing to give them another try since the friends we were with really like the place.
